## Setting up Git Credentials
-------------------------------------------------------------
# Add your github username as the global Git username in your container
git config --global user.name [username_from_github]

# Add the Email associated with your github account as the global Git Email in your container
git config --global user.email [email_from_github]  

# Stores credentials in plain text.
git config --global credential.helper store

# Check your Git settings
git config --list 

------------------------------------------------------------------
# Change our branch name from “master” to “main” to align with Github terminology
git branch -M main

# Connect our local repository to the remote where HTTP-link is your own respiratory
git remote add origin [the-HTTP-link]

# Updates the remote repository from your local repository
git push -u origin main

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Ensures Git uses the default merging strategy
git config pull.rebase false

# Add a file to .gitignore which already exists in the git history
git rm --cached [name_of_file_added_to_.gitignore]

# The repository will now be downloaded as a folder within the current directory in your terminal
git clone [the-HTTP-link]
